var tipuesearch = {"pages": [{'title': 'About', 'text': 'This is  https://github.com/mdecourse/cmstemplate \n 目前的 cmsimde 在編輯器下方新增一個 csave 按鈕, 意即 collabrative save, 當動態網際管理系統在多人同時維護登入維護網頁內容時, 編輯各頁面時段, 該頁面可能已經改版, 因此使用 csave 按鈕存檔時, 會導入當下最新的該頁面內容, 並試圖與編輯中的頁面內容進行合併. \n 使用 csave 按鈕存檔無法刪除頁面資料. \n 使用 Edit All 模式, 無法使用 csave 按鈕（尚未測試). \n \n', 'tags': '', 'url': 'About.html'}, {'title': 'HW1', 'text': '', 'tags': '', 'url': 'HW1.html'}, {'title': 'Page.85~96', 'text': '', 'tags': '', 'url': 'Page.85~96.html'}, {'title': 'page.85', 'text': 'while fiber-optic cable is great for its speed，distance and security，it hasn`t yet become commonplace in most networks.instead，we are still using the same type of cabling we have using for the past two to three decades--twsited pair.Twsited pair cable is most popular physical LAN media in the world today.Each cable contains four pairs of individually insulated strands of copper wire.Each pair is twsited together to minimize the amount of electromagnetic interference(EMI).The more twsite in the cable ，the less EMI there will be.Twsited Pair cable is broken up into two type:unshielded twsited pair (UTP) and shielded twsited pair. \n 雖然光纖電纜的速度、距離和安全性能非常優異，但是它仍然在許多電腦工作的地方並不普及。儘管如此，我們仍舊用某些類型的電纜，將它放在一些電纜壽命需要超過二十年至三十年的地方-雙絞線。雙絞線是現在世界上最火紅的物理性LAN介質.每一條電纜包含了四對獨立絕緣的銅線。每一對絞合在一起，用最大能力減緩電磁波的干擾。電纜線有越多雙絞線包含在裡面，電磁波就越難發生。雙絞線有兩種類型:非屏蔽式和屏蔽式。 \n Shielded twsited pair cable is built very similarly to unshielded twsited pair，except that the pair of wires are also surrouded by a metallic shielded (like foil).This outer foil shielded minimize \n the EMI to which the cable exposed.This increases the security and reliability of the cable .Unfortunately，however，this also increases the cost of the cable，so it is typecally used only in high-production envirements where the extra security is worth the extra cost. \n 遮蔽式雙絞線和非遮蔽式雙絞線的構造非常相似，那它們有甚麼地方不一樣呢?它們不同之處在於屏蔽雙絞線中成對的電線也被金屬屏蔽層(例如說金屬箔)包覆，外部箔屏蔽層可大幅減輕電纜因暴露在電磁波的干擾中所受的傷害，這個方法大幅增加了電纜的安全性和可靠度，但很不幸的是，這個方法會增加額外的成本，所以在需要多出來的成本產生額外的高安全性的那些高生產力環境比較常見。 \n The more common type of cabling is unshielded twsited pair cable.Instead of using extra shielded，this cable relies on the twsiting of its copper pairs to minimize the effects of EMI.Each twsited pair is twsited to insulate itself from the other pairs，and becuase there is no additional shielding，it\'s available at a lower cost than STP.Therefore，UTP is most common media of choice for small office,home office,residential and many commercial networks. \n 非遮蔽雙絞線類型比遮蔽式雙絞線類型的普及率還高，而且該類型的雙絞線不需要另外的遮蔽，它依靠銅線絞合來產生抵抗電磁波干擾的最大效能，每一個雙絞線經過絞合後將自身與其它絞線絕緣，再來因為它沒有額外的覆層，所以可以用比遮蔽行雙絞線低的價格取得它。因此非遮蔽型雙絞線對小型辦公室、家庭工廠、住宅和許多商業網路最常選擇的大眾媒體。 \n Twsited pair cable is categorized based on category (cat)number.For example,cat 3,category 3,is the oldest type of cable that we use.It was introducted back in the 1980s and 1990s for use in the first star topologies.The maximum throughput or bandwidth of cat 3 cablingis only 10 Mbps(megabits per second).The cat 3,like all twsited pair cabling,can\'t go ferther than 100 meters without using a repeater,switch,or active hub to amplify the signal.This limited distance is attributable to the copper wiring in these cables. As the signal travels over the copper wire,the netural resistance to wire decreases the signal\'s strength,and it eventually become too weak for the distant end to receive.For this reason,there is a 100 meter limitation when building and designing a twsited pair network. \n 雙絞線是以類別加數字來做分類。舉例來說，我們使用最早的電纜類型是類別3( cat 3)。這要從80年代和90年代用於第一批星型拓樸結構開始介紹起，cat 3電纜的最大吞吐量或頻寬只有10Mbps。cat 3電纜和其它雙絞線電纜一樣，使用中繼器、交換機或有源集線器來放大信號，cat 3才能超過100米。這個有限的距離歸因於在電纜中的銅線。當在銅線上傳輸信號時，銅線的自然電阻會減弱信號的強度，減弱到最後會無法接收遠端資訊。也因為如此，這100公尺的長度變成是建構或設計光纖網路時的阻礙。 \n Cat 5 cables were an improvement on the older cat 3 cables and contain more twists, giving them more shielding from EMI and a maximum bandwidth of 100 Mbps. Cat 5e, or cat 5 enhanced, increased the speed of the maximum throughput to one Gbps, or 1000 Mbps, and became a gap filler until cat 6 cabling became commonplace. \n Cat 5電纜比Cat 3電纜更進一步擁有更多的雙絞線，這些雙絞線讓Cat 5電纜抵抗電磁波干擾時有更強的能力，而且擁有最大吞吐量來到100Mbps或1000Mbps的效能，並且填補在Cat 6電纜更普及化前的空缺。 \n Cat 6a overcomes the 37-55 meter limitation of cat 6 when used in 10GBaseT. Cat 7, the newest standard, is shielded and provides connections up to 10 Gbps with a maximum distance of 100 meters. “Cat 7 and cat 7a cabling will be used for backbone connections between servers within a data center” and “provide an alternative to using fiber-optic cabling within the data center”\xa0 \n Cat 6ay在10GBaseT使用時的限制比Cat 6超過37~55公尺，來到137公尺~155公尺。最新的標準Cat 7"有屏蔽，且能提供最大為10Mbps的帶寬、100公尺的距離。"Cat 7和Cat 7a將用於數據中心內伺服器的主幹連接"並且"提供一個讓數據中心使用光纖電纜的選擇"。 \n All cable categories up to cat 5e and cat 6a have a maximum distance of 100 meters. When used in 10GBaseT, the maximum distance for cat 6 is 55 meters. Cat 7 is shielded and exceeds the 100 meter limit. As the category of the cable increases, so do the number of twists per inch and the frequency range, allowing for more data and improved protection against EMI. Best practice for copper cabling is\xa0 not \xa0 to run cable lengths to the maximum because attenuation will reduce data capacity. \n 在所有電纜線的類別中，能傳輸最大距離100公尺的電纜線只有Cat 5e和Cat 6a。當使用Cat 6傳輸10GBaseT的資料時，它最多只能傳輸55公尺。Cat 7因為擁有遮蔽的技術，所以它能超過100公尺的傳輸限制。隨著纜線類別的增加，每英吋的捻數和頻率也跟著增加以支持更多、更快的資料傳輸和更好的保護以防止受到電磁波的干擾。最好的銅線不是越長越好，而是傳輸越多資料以達到越高的效率才越好。 \n Twisted pair cables come with three main types of connectors. The first is the RJ-45 connector, which is an eight-pin connector used in Ethernet networks. Even though most Ethernet networks use only four pins, the RJ-45 provides eight pins for future use and capabilities. The first four pins are used to transmit (two pins) and receive (two pins). \n 雙絞線有三種類型的連接器。第一種是RJ-45連接器，它是用乙太網路的八針連接器，儘管大部分的乙太網路都使用四針連接器，RJ-45仍因應未來的使用和效能而提供八針連接器，前四個引針中的兩個是用來傳輸，另外兩個則是接收訊息。 \n The RJ-11 connector is used in the standard telephone system. The RJ-11 is a six-pin connector, but commonly only two pins are used for a telephone (transmit and receive). If you have a two-line phone, then four pins are used: two pins to transmit and two pins to receive. \n RJ-11連接器通常用在標準的的電話系統，它有6針連接器，但是電話通常只會用兩針連接器(用來傳輸和接收訊息)，如果您有一個雙線電話，則另外四線連接器中的兩線用來傳輸訊號，剩下兩線用於接收訊號。 \n Finally, the DB-9 connector is used for RS-232 signals. This connector looks like a standard serial connector. It is used commonly for asynchronous serial communications, like connecting to an external modem. In modern networks, you will see this type of connector on a “rollover cable.” A rollover cable has a DB-9 on one side (which is connected to your laptop’s serial port), and an RJ-45 connector on the other side (which is used to connect to Cisco routers and switches to do administration tasks) \n 最後，DB-9連接器用於傳輸和接收RS-232信號，它看起來像標準的串聯連接器，通常用於異步串聯異步串聯通信，譬如連接至外部的調製解調器。在現代網路世界中，您將會看到這類型的連接器在"轉換電路"之上。一個轉換電纜中的一側有DB-9連接器(它是用來連接筆電的端子接口)，然後一個RJ-45連接器在其它地方(用來連接Cisco路由器和交換機以執行管理任務) \n A straight-through cable is a type of twisted pair cable that is used in local area networks to connect a computer to a network hub, such as a router. This type of cable is also sometimes called a patch cable. Both ends of the cable have an identical pinout, hence the name “straight-through.” A crossover cable switches the pinouts of the two ends of the cable, making the transmit and receive pins alternate on the two ends. This allows two workstations to connect directly to each other without the need for a hub, switch, or router. \n 直通電纜是一種使用於區域網路連接到網路集線器的雙絞線，像是路由器。這類型的電纜有時也稱為跳線。在電纜的兩端有相同的引出線，所以稱作"直通"。交叉電纜切換電纜兩端的分配，讓兩端的引出線擁有輸出或接收的選擇，這樣的方式可令工作站不需要路由器、交換器和網路集線器的導引就可連接到其他人的電腦。 \n', 'tags': '', 'url': 'page.85.html'}, {'title': 'page.86', 'text': 'Coaxial cable is a much older media technology. Coaxial cable, also known as coax for short, is composed of two conductors. The inner conductor, which is known as the insulated conductor (center wire), is the copper wire over which data is passed. The outer conductor is the braided metal shield and aids in protecting the inner wire from physical injury and the effects of EMI. Much like the shielding we saw in shielded twisted pair, the outer shield helps keep electromagnetic interference out of the data’s path. Between the inner conductor and the outer shield, we find an insulated core that prevents any data transfer between the inner core and outer shield. The outside of the cable is made of a flexible plastic jacket, much like the twisted pair cabling. Coaxial cabling was included in the first Ethernet standard as 10Base5 (thicknet) and continued to be used throughout updates as 10Base2 (thinnet) as well as being most commonly used in bus and ring networks. UTP cabling however, is easier to work with in a star topology and is significantly less expensive. \n 同軸電纜是一種較成熟的媒體科技。同軸電纜有時也使用較短的名稱-同軸來稱呼它，它是由兩個導體所組成。在裡面的導體是很有名的絕緣導體，它是用來傳輸資料的銅線。外部的導體擁有保護層來保護內部導體以防止其受電磁波干擾的影響。我們所見到的遮蔽型雙絞線，外層的遮蔽物幫助資料傳輸時避免受到電磁波的影響。在內層和外層的遮蔽層之間，我們發現一個交換碼以避免資料在內層和外層遮蔽物之間做傳輸。就像是大多數的雙絞線，在直通電纜的外層包覆著可拆卸的塑膠覆層。直通電纜out \n \n There are three dominant coaxial cable types. The RG-6 is commonly used by cable TV companies to connect individual homes to the TV network. These cables are thick and usually used for outside connections to withstand the effects of the weather. The RG-58 is a type of coaxial cable that was heavily used in early 10Base2 (thinnet) networks, such as bus and ring topologies. Finally, the RG-59 is the traditional coaxial cable used to carry composite video between two nearby devices, such as your TV and the cable box. If you are a cable Internet user, this is also used to carry the WAN connection from your wall jack to your cable modem. \n \n 總共有三種同軸纜線的形式。RG-6常被有線電視公司拿來連接每一個家庭的電視網路。這些電纜又粗又在外面連接，因此很容易受到天氣影響。RG-58是用於早期的10Base2的其中一種重型同軸電纜，像是鈴型拓譜結構和總線網路。最後，RG-59用於連接收音機到兩個附近的設備之間的傳統同軸電纜，就像是你家的電視和機上盒的連接。如果你是一個有線網路的使用者，這也是一個可用於從牆壁插孔連接到你的電纜調製解調器的攜帶型WAN連接器。 \n While there were three types of cables, there are only two types of common connectors used with coaxial cable. The first is called BNC, from the name Bayonet Neill-Concelman. Sometimes people also call this the British Naval connector, because the BNC was heavily used by the British in their shipboard radio systems. This connector was commonly used in early Ethernet networks and it has a “push and twist” type of connector to secure the cable to the network device. \n 雖然有三種電纜，但是我們通常用在連接器的電纜只有兩種，第一種是由Bayonet Neill-Concelman的名字縮寫為BNC，有時候人們稱它為英國海軍連接器，因為BNC曾經使用於英國海軍的船用通訊系統。這種連接器常用於早期的乙太網路，並擁有"推壓式"連接器以確保電纜有連接到網路設備。 \n The F-type connector is the modern type of coaxial cable connector. It is typically used for cable TV and cable modem connections. It is connected by screwing the connector onto a threaded jack to secure the connection. \n F類型的連接器是一種現代的同軸電纜連接器。它經常用於有線電視和有線數據機的連接。它用螺絲起子將連接器鎖緊以確保有無連接。 \n', 'tags': '', 'url': 'page.86.html'}, {'title': 'page.87', 'text': 'When we compare the advantages and disadvantages of fiber-optic cables and copper (twisted pair) cables, we have to consider that fiber-optic has a higher bandwidth (measured in Gbps or Tbps), it can carry its signal many miles without the need of a repeater, it is immune to the effects of EMI, and it has much better security than traditional twisted pair cables. However, twisted pair cabling does hold some advantages of its own. For one, it is much less expensive than fiber-optic cabling. Also, copper wiring is much easier to install, taking only a few hours to learn. Finally, twisted pair cabling can be created and terminated using inexpensive tools. For example, a complete copper wiring toolset can be bought online for less than $50, while a complete fiber-optic kit may cost $1000 or more. For these reasons, copper has remained the dominant media in most local area networks. \n 當我們考慮銅做成的電纜(雙絞線)和光纖電纜的優勢和劣勢時，我們必須考慮光纖電纜有更大的帶寬(以gbp和tbp作為單位)，它可以不需要中繼器就可將信號傳輸到更遠的距離，而且比較不受電磁波的影響，因此更安全。但是雙絞線電纜依舊保有一些優勢，例如它比雙絞線電纜更便宜。而且銅纜較容易安裝，只需要幾小時就可完成。最後，雙絞線電纜會因為廉價的工具被創造而停止使用，舉例來說，一個完整的銅線網路在網路上只賣不到50美金，而光纖電纜可能比1000美金還貴，因為這些原因，銅纜一直是許多區域網路的主要媒介。 \n', 'tags': '', 'url': 'page.87.html'}, {'title': 'page.88', 'text': 'Because of the wide variety of cable and connector types, there is sometimes a need to convert from one type of media to another. For example, if you have to make a connection between two LANs in buildings that are located one mile apart, but your network uses Cat 5e, UTP cabling, how can you make that connection? When you look at your routers, you find they only accept RJ-45 connections, but you know that you cannot run a Cat 5e cable more than 100 meters. How can you solve this problem? With a media converter. \n 因為有許多種連接器和電纜的類別，因此有時候需要從一個媒體轉換成另一個媒體，舉例來說，你將兩條LAN建構在1英里的兩端，但是你的網路是用Cat 5e和非屏蔽式電纜，那你要怎麼做連接?當你看著你的路由器，你發現它可以連接RJ-45的纜線，但是你知道你不可能讓運作的Cat 5e超過100公尺，那你要怎麼用一個媒介轉接器解決這個問題? \n Using a media converter, you can convert your RJ-45 connection into an ST, SC, or LC fiber connection, as shown in the image below. Then, you run the one-mile fiber cable to the other building, and use a media converter to convert from the ST, SC, or LC fiber connection back to the RJ-45 the other router requires. Because this is a simple, “dumb” device, it simply converts whatever is received on the first media type and repeats it back out the second media type. Common types of media converters are from Ethernet (copper) to fiber-optic (and back) or coaxial to fiber-optic (and back). \n 你可以在使用媒介轉換器時將你的RJ-45轉接到ST、SC或LC連接電纜，然後將一英里的光纖電纜連接到其它建築物，然後再用一個媒介轉換器將ST、SC或LC光纖電纜轉回另一台路由器所需的RJ-45，由於這是一個簡單的"接收器"設備，因此它會轉換接收到的訊號，再重複播放至第二個媒體類型。通常媒體轉換器會放在乙太網路到光纖電纜或同軸電纜之間(或相反)。 \n', 'tags': '', 'url': 'page.88.html'}, {'title': 'page.90', 'text': 'In this module, we are going to discuss how the various Ethernet standards developed over time. We will also discuss why there is a need for these standards and the effect of these standards on the industry. In addition, we are going to cover various types of network media standards. We will cover 10Base-T (802.3i, 1990) as well as 100Base-T and 1000Base-T (1GBASE-T or 1 GigE) Ethernet standards, which are most commonly found in current office networks. We will discover how to plan a basic network connection using 100BaseT. Finally, we will cover differences between Ethernet and TCP/IP. \n 在本節當中，我們將隨著時間的進展而逐步討論開發各種標準的乙太網路，我們也會討論為甚麼我們需要這些標準的乙太網路以及這些標準的乙太網路對工業的影響。再來，我們將介紹各種標準的乙太網路，包含像是很常在辦公網路中的10BaseT以及100BaseT和1000BaseT的標準乙太網路。我們將知道怎麼用100BaseT布建一個基本的網路架構。我們將介紹乙太網路和TCP/IP的差異。 \n', 'tags': '', 'url': 'page.90.html'}, {'title': 'page.92', 'text': 'The nature of half-duplex transmission brought about the need for CSMA/CD, which works by allowing all devices to transmit data whenever they wish. The carrier sense portion means that the device “listens” to the network first to find a “break” in the conversation. If the device doesn’t hear other devices transmitting, then it begins its transmission. Multiple access refers to every device having equal access to the network at all times. This is unlike the token ring network in which each device had to wait for the signal (token) before transmitting. Finally, we have collision detection as part of the CSMA/CD control method. If, by chance, two devices both were ready to transmit, they “listened” to the network for a “lull” in the conversation, and both started transmitting at the same time, the devices are able to detect that they both transmitted at the same time and caused a collision. \n 半雙工這種需要所有可讓它傳輸資料的設備伴隨著對CSMA/CD的需求營運商必須知道這意味著該設備會"監聽"網路對話中的"斷點"，如果該設備沒有接收到其他設備所傳輸的資料時，它們便會開始傳輸資料。多話訪問具有對個別設備平等的訪問優先權。這不像是令牌網路一樣必須等到所有設備都傳輸完資料後才能做訪問。最後，我暪將碰撞檢測視為CSMA/CD的控制方法其中之一，如果有機會兩個設備都準備備好要傳輸資料，它們會"監聽"網路對話中"失效"的部分，並且會同時傳輸資料，該設備得以檢測是否碰撞且在同一時間傳送訊號。 \n The concept of collision domains is very important in Ethernet standards, because collision domains determine how fast the network will actually operate. As shown in the previous diagram, collisions cause the devices to back off, wait, and then retransmit. If this occurs too often, valuable time is wasted and frequent collisions bring network speeds down - somewhat like a traffic jam on an interstate. All devices on a shared Ethernet segment are members of a single collision domain. If you are running Thicknet or Thinnet (coaxial bus networks), then all devices on a single cable are in the same collision domain. If you are using a star topology with unshielded twisted pair, then all devices connected to a singular hub (since hubs repeat the transmissions on every port) are part of a single collision domain operating at half-duplex. \n 衝突域的概念在標準乙太網路中非常重要，因為它決定了網路實際運作的速度。衝突導致退回，等待，然後重新傳輸，如果這個情況經常發生，會導致網速變慢而浪費時間，就像是州際公路上的交通堵塞一樣。共享乙太網路上的所有設備都是單個衝突域的成員。如果運行的是Thicknet或Thinnet(同軸總線網路)，那所有設備在同一個纜線上都有相同的衝突域。如果你用星型拓樸結構搭配非遮蔽式雙絞線，那所有設備在半雙攻上都有單一個衝突域以連接至單一個樞紐(因為樞紐會不斷的重複傳輸至每一個設備)。 \n To prevent collisions in the network, the collision domains must be kept small. One option is to use bridge connecting hubs to break up the collision domains. However, an even more effective method of doing this is to use switches. Remember, hubs create collision domains while switches break up collision domains but also create broadcast domains. \n 為了防止網路中有衝突發生，衝突域都應盡量減小。一個消除衝突域的方法是用連接器接上集線器，但是，交換器擁有更多更能減小衝突域的方法。記得，集線器創造衝突域而交換器消除衝突域，而創造廣播域。 \n Ethernet switches are preferred over hubs due to their ability to solve the collision domain issue. For the most part, switches have replace hubs; it is rare to see hubs and bridges in current networks because of the superior operation of switches and the overall price reduction. \n 由於乙太網路擁有比其他設備更強大的解決衝突域問題的能力，在大多數時候，集線器可被更換成交換器，因為交換器的價格低且擁有更強大的合作能力，所以在當前的網路中，集線器和連接器是非常罕見的。 \n Each switch port is its own collision domain and supports full duplex (simultaneous TX and RX) when operating at 100Mbs or faster and using CAT5 cabling or better. This prevents any chance of collision, eliminates the need for CSMA/CD, and increases the speed of the network dramatically compared to hubs. \n 每一個交換機端口會因為用100Mbps或更快的速度將全雙工纜線與Cat5或更好的纜線連接起來而產生自己的衝突域。我們必須要用CSMA/CD來消除衝突域發生的機會，而且與集線器相比，它增加網路的速率更加明顯。 \n', 'tags': '', 'url': 'page.92.html'}, {'title': 'Page.93', 'text': 'Finally, we need to discuss the various standards we use in Ethernet in terms of bandwidth and distance limitations. \n 最後，我們將討論使用標準乙太網路的帶寬與距離的限制。 \n The Ethernet standard also determines the type of cable, its bandwidth, and its distance limitation. It is important to know these standards, especially those that relate to a category 3, 5, 5e, and 6 cabling standard. \n 使用甚麼類型的纜線決定了乙太網路的帶寬和距離限制，你必須要知道這些標準數據，以及這些有關於類型3、5、5e、6的纜線之標準數據。 \n When discussing data flow and speed, the two terms referred to are bandwidth and throughput. Often used interchangeably, the two terms are different and need to be understood. Simply put, bandwidth is the theoretical maximum of the given standard, whereas throughput is the actual potential in a real-world scenario. Many factors affect actual throughput, such as half-duplex vs. full-duplex, cable length, and quality. Both bandwidth and throughput are measured in bits per second (bps) with the prefix K (kilobit), M (megabit), or G (gigabit). Each Ethernet category (cat) cable supports a different Ethernet standard and thereby determines the bandwidth capacity or maximum throughput. The table below shows the bandwidth according to Ethernet type. \n 在討論數據流和速度時，我們用兩個術語來代表這兩個情況-帶寬和吞吐量，這兩個術語可互換使用，它們是不一樣的東西且必須知道，簡而言之，帶寬是理論上可承受的最大標準量，而最大吞吐量是實際上可承受的數據量，許多因素會影響實際的吞吐量，譬如使用的是半雙工還是全雙工，纜線長度及品質。帶寬和最大吞吐量均以每秒多少prefix K (kilobit)、多少megabit或gigabit的儲存量來衡量。每一種乙太網路線都有它配合的標準乙太網路，而且會有決定性的影響帶寬和最大吞吐量。 \n', 'tags': '', 'url': 'Page.93.html'}, {'title': 'page.94', 'text': 'Now that you have a general understanding of networking hardware, application of standards for LANs (local area networks) and WANs (wide area networks), and the limitations of the media used, you should be able to plan adding a network node to an already existing network. For example, you could add a new computer to your company’s wired LAN. In such situations, the majority of the hardware installation is plug and play (PnP), but you still have to know that the hardware and media chosen are correct, configure software settings for network access, and verify the new hardware will function properly to allow user access to all network resources. \n 現在你對媒體使用時的限制、使用區域網路和外部網路的應用程式還有網路設備的硬體有一般的認識，那你應該可以規劃網路節點增添至網路上。譬如說，你可以將新電腦加入你公司的區域網路中，在這種情況下絕大多數的設備都是即插即用，但你仍需要知道怎樣挑選硬體和媒體才是正確的，讓網路進入的正確軟體設定，以及確認當使用者使用所有網路的資源時，能有效且快速的運作。 \n Current technology in most small office/home office (SOHO) environments will have auto-sensing networking hardware. There are older switches and routers that still remain in some networks that do not have the ability to run at 100/1000BaseT, so check your network documentation! \n 絕大多數的小型辦公室和家庭工廠的環境都有自動偵測網路軟體的現代科技。但是他們仍有一些是使用舊型的交換器和路由器，以至於無法在100BaseT或1000BaseT中運作，所以請你在使用網路資源前檢查你的網路檔案!', 'tags': '', 'url': 'page.94.html'}]};